wt.associativity

Interface CopyEquivalenceLinkForwardDelegate


  • public interface CopyEquivalenceLinkForwardDelegate
    The purpose of this delegate is to copy the existing Equivalence links whenever an object is iterated. This interface should be implemented by customized implementations.

    Supported API: true

    Extendable: true

    • Method Summary

      • copyEquivalenceLinkForward

        void copyEquivalenceLinkForward(Iterated old_iterated,
                                Iterated new_iterated,
                                wt.associativity.NCServerHolder nc_server_holder,
                                boolean process_children,
                                boolean can_update_downstream_context)
                         throws WTException
        Copy forward the equivalence links whenever an object is iterated.

        Supported API: true
        Parameters:
        old_iterated - Previous iteration
        new_iterated - New iteration
        nc_server_holder - The navigation criteria to use to filter the iterations for the masters used
        process_children - Whether to duplicate equivalence links at first level children too
        can_update_downstream_context - Whether to set the downstream context of the new equivalence link to the view of the new iteration
        Throws:
        WTException

      • copyEquivalenceLinkForward

        @Deprecated
boolean[] copyEquivalenceLinkForward(Iterated[] curIterateds,
                                                 Iterated[] newIterateds,
                                                 wt.associativity.NCServerHolder[] ncsHolders,
                                                 ViewReference[] newDownstreamContexts)
                                          throws WTException
        Deprecated. - This method was used by applets and no longer used OOTB by any application code. So recommended not to use this.
        This method will carry forward the existing upstream equivalent links from current part to new part which have valid downstream context for the current EC. Also it will reset the downstream context with new context on duplicated link

        Supported API: true
        Parameters:
        curIterateds - Previous iteration
        newIterateds - New iteration
        ncsHolders - The navigation criteria to use to filter the equivalent links with valid downstream context
        newDownstreamContexts - The context to be set on the duplicated links on the new parts
        Throws:
        WTException
